It's not really fair to call it 2160i (interlaced), because they aren't alternating even/odd lines (which would look awful), but rather it's "2D interlacing" at the pixel level.  It looks okay at a distance, but it's not true progressive 4K.

I'd like to propose a new term: "2160c".  This is the vertical resolution of 4K, but with an added "c", for checkerboard.  So you have 1080p (progressive), 2160p (true 4K), but then 2160c (checkerboard).  This is for e.g. PS4 Pro games, which render every other pixel in 4K.
More on checkerboard rendering: https://t.co/iHm2tZCQIY
